@NODE "What"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rexx - What Is It?@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}


What is it?

I develop the script at time when I was doing a lot of split and join of 
large file to and from a floppy disk.

Using opus directory as GUI interface and Rexx as Join or link to the split 
and join programmes.

This made life a lot easier as I did not often opened a shell and type in 
the commands to to this function.
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rexx - Requirements@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
To use SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rexx you will need:-

- AmigaDOS/Workbench 3.0 or higher (Does anyone still use WB 2.0 or earlier?)

- Joinz & Splitz version 1992 ASDG 1.0.1 (11.5.92)
    ***(NOT INCLUDED IN THIS ARCHIVE)***

- ARexx installed on your system

- Dopus directory version 4.12
 
To the best of my knowledge SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rexx will work on 
@{B}ANY @{UB}Amiga equipped with AmigaDOS/Workbench 3.0 or higher.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "How"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rex - How To Use It@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}@{U}Manual Installation@{UB}@{UU}:-

1. Copy "SuperJoin.rexx & SuperSplit.rexx" into the Splitz and Joinz 
   directory.

2. Copy the file "SuperJoin&Split.guide" to wherever you like to keep your
   documents.

3.  I've enclosed example of how to do this as an opus directory V4.12 
    configuration file.  You will find it on Button labelled Split & Join 
    of how to set up for a single Lister.  And a gif images of the 
    configuration screen setting up opus to run SuperJoin.rexx & 
    SuperSplit.rexx scripts.  Within the filename of the image for the 
    single Lister are 01, and for the double Lister 02.


@{B}General setting for opus file manager@{UB}

In opus you most marked the list of options:-

CD Source
Directory Opus to Front
No filename quote
Outpout Window

All other settings are set to default.


They are two ways of setting up.

@{B}First way - working in a single Lister   (Splitz_01.gif & joinz_01.gif)@{UB}

This stores split files in the same directory as the large file.  So make 
should that you got enough room for split files.  As the programmes does not 
checked for this.  And a Split filename do is not occur in the directory.

As the first parameter of the script should be {f}, following the filename 
of the script.


@{B}Second way - working in a double Lister   (Splitz_02.gif & joinz_02.gif)@{UB}

The stores the Spitz files in the destination directory.  Make sure that 
you've got enough room in your destination directory to store split files.


@{B}Working with floppy disks@{UB}

You were need some sort of text editor to this operation.  In the programme 
SuperSplit.rexx change the code in the programme to the below code.

/* Execute the splitz program with parament */

StorePath SourceFileName DirectoryName SizeOfFile PAUSE

say('This real name is 'SourceFileName' split filename is 'DeFileName)

Size of chunk

The chunk size is based on bytes and a set to 840000 in size and based 
around double density disk.  It is a bit short in case there are some disk 
errors.  To change size type a new value to replace the old value in the 
Rexx programme.

/* Find Out the Disk Size capture */

SizeOfFile=840000

Make sure that you do not used disk already occupied with files on disk, 
or unformat disk and wrong size format disk (720K IBM Disk).

They are two parameters the first parameter of the script should be {f} 
and the second parameter {d}, following the filename of the script.


@{B}A bit more information on installing@{UB}

The line which activate the ARexx script.  First call up the ARexx 
interpreter which then giving by parameter the storage location to call 
SuperJoin.rexx or SuperSplit.rexx programme with parameters.

@ENDNODE

